# Gemma & Open WebUI Setup Complete

Your local AI environment is now fully set up and running entirely on your RTX 4060, completely private and offline!

## What was installed
1. **Ollama**: The engine running the models locally.
2. **Gemma 4**: Google's highly capable model (fully downloaded).
3. **Open WebUI**: A beautiful web interface that runs on your local network.

## How to Access Open WebUI

The Web UI server is currently running in the background.

### From this PC:
Open your web browser and go to:
[http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)

*Note: The very first time you open this page, it will ask you to "Sign Up". Because it's running offline, this just creates your local admin account. Just enter any name, email, and password you want to use for your local profile!*

### From your Phone (on the same Wi-Fi):
To chat from your phone, open your mobile browser and type in your PC's local IP address followed by `:8080`:
`http://192.168.29.90:8080`

> [!TIP]
> You can bookmark this link on your phone's home screen. It will feel just like having the ChatGPT app, but it runs securely off your PC's GPU without costing any tokens!

## Interacting via Terminal
If you ever just want to quickly ask a question from the terminal without opening the UI, you can always open Command Prompt or PowerShell and type:
```bash
ollama run gemma4
```

> [!NOTE]
> Open WebUI is a background process. If you ever restart your PC and want to launch the UI again, simply open a terminal and run `C:\Users\zacca\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python311\Scripts\open-webui.exe serve`. (You can easily create a desktop shortcut for this!).
